1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with the problem of AI agents disobeying regulations and proposes a solution using reinforcement learning and game theory. 
2. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper specifically focuses on multi-agent reinforcement learning and proposes a mechanism for regulating the behavior of non-compliant agents. 
3. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper uses game theory to formulate the problem and analyze the proposed solution. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses deep multi-agent reinforcement learning algorithms to conduct simulated experiments. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - Although the paper does not explicitly deal with robotics, the proposed solution could potentially be applied to multi-robot systems where regulations need to be enforced.
